Creating a design process for a device with a variety of materials and techniques. Subjects of the previously studied specialty are integrated. Completed with a larger product with a portfolio.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is to enable the student to acquire a self-contained, practical-oriented, technological-creative product. Teaching through subject is to achieve the student's willingness to implement creatively acquired professional knowledge and skills at which the working device will be created. Students will be taught to work with relevant sources, analyze the necessary materials and techniques, and find suitable solutions. A portfolio is created from the integrated product.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1.	1.	Has the ability to integrate the knowledge and skills acquired in various specialties; 2.	Can solve tasks related to product creation and find and solve problems;  3.	Can analyze and synthesize new creative solutions for product design process.  4.	Has the ability to correctly compile the portfolio; 5.	Can present and defend the product.
